You can use the floating format toolbar to style and format the elements. It appears at the top of the selection.
Styling headings and quotes isn't allowed. You'll notice the style buttons become disabled when you select a heading or a quote.
You'll notice a floating toolbar with a "+" symbol to the left at the start of a new paragraph. This is the floating block toolbar and it can be used to insert dividers, images, and code blocks.
This editor also supports latex to help write better technical articles.
To create a latex node, simply enclose the text within '$'. This will create an inline latex node like so:
To create a block latex node, enclose the text within '$$'.
If you double click on the latex node, the floating equation editor pops up. You can use it to edit the node and toggle between block and inline formats.
